          h2 GraphGist Winter Challenge

        .panel-body
          p Wintertime - GraphGist time, like last year we want to sweeten your long winter evenings and encourage you to participate in our Winter-Challenge to create the most helpful and ingenious graph models and example queries.

          p This year we'd like to focus on use-cases that graph databases are best suited to handle:

          ul
            li
              | Solve the JOIN pain. Complex 
              strong
                a(href="/#!/domains/Relational Models") relational models
              |  and queries converted to a graph model
            li
              | Make a wish come true. 
              strong
                a(href="/#!/domains/Recommendations") Recommendations
              |  for anything imaginable
            li
              | What if Winter was coming? 
              strong
                a(href="/#!/domains/Impact Analysis") Impact Analysis
              |  on dependent information networks
            li
              | A library of everything. 
              strong
                a(href="/#!/domains/Content and Asset Management") Content and asset management
            li
              | Find my special star. Creative 
              strong
                a(href="/#!/domains/Graph Search and Insights") Graph Search and Insights
            li
              | Amaze us - 
              strong Give your best
              |  and show us a graph application beyond imagination

          p The competition runs until January 12th, We announce the winners by the end of January.

          p For each of the 6 categories there will be a main prize of $500.

          p
            |  To celebrate the new challenge, we launch our GraphGist Portal, thanks to 
            a(href="http://www.kennybastani.com/") Kenny Bastani
            | , 
            a(href="https://github.com/whatSocks") May Lim
            |   and 
            a(href="http://www.brian-underwood.codes/") Brian Underwood
            |  for working hard on creating this amazing resource of all great GraphGists ever submitted.

          p
            | Just 
            a(href="/#!/gists/submit") send in
            |  your GraphGist submission until January 12, choose the category and provide the necessary details, then you automatically qualify for participation.

